.TH "batadv_frag_skb_buffer" 9 "batadv_frag_skb_buffer" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
batadv_frag_skb_buffer \- buffer fragment for later merge
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "bool" batadv_frag_skb_buffer
.BI "(struct sk_buff **skb "  ","
.BI "struct batadv_orig_node *orig_node_src "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "skb" 12
skb to buffer
.IP "orig_node_src" 12
originator that the skb is received from
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Add fragment to buffer and merge fragments if possible.

There are three possible outcomes: 1) Packet is merged: Return true and
set *skb to merged packet; 2) Packet is buffered: Return true and set *skb
to NULL; 3) Error: Return false and free skb.
.SH "RETURN"
true when the packet is merged or buffered, false when skb is not
used.
